# IPFreeTV - AI Context File

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
NativeScript Android IPTV app with 300+ Indian TV channels. Built with NativeScript Core 9.x, ExoPlayer for video, TailwindCSS for styling. Tab navigation: Categories, Favorites, All Channels.

## STRUCTURE
```
app/
├── assets/json/IndianChannels.json      # 822 channels [{id, tvg-logo, group-title, name, url}]
├── common/                              # constants.ts, helpers.ts, store/
├── components/                          # action-bar/, channel-list/
├── screens/                             # 7 pages including video-page with ExoPlayer
app.ts                                   # Entry point
app.css                                  # Tailwind + CSS vars (--primary: #08CB00)
```

## KEY PATTERNS
- **Navigation**: TabView → Frames → Pages with context passing
- **Platform**: `__ANDROID__`/`__IOS__` macros, Android orientation control
- **Data**: Categories from `group-title` split by ';', favorites in ApplicationSettings
- **Video**: Fullscreen toggle hides system UI, landscape orientation
- **UI**: Custom action bar with search, observable ViewModels with `fromObject`

## IMPORTANT FILES
1. `app/screens/main-page.xml` - Tab navigation (3 tabs)
2. `app/screens/video-page/` - ExoPlayer integration with fullscreen
3. `app/components/action-bar/` - Reusable header with search
4. `app/common/helpers.ts` - getAppVersion(), compareSemver()
5. `package.json` - Deps: @nativescript/core, @nstudio/nativescript-exoplayer

## STYLING
- Colors: primary(#08CB00), secondary(#253900), text(#000000), bg(#EEEEEE)
- Fonts: Roboto regular/bold
- Tailwind utility classes in XML

## BUILD/RUN
```bash
npm install
ns run android    # Android only (iOS untested)
```

## UPDATE THIS FILE WHEN:
- Adding/removing screens or components
- Changing dependencies in package.json
- Modifying project structure
- Adding new data patterns or utilities

